The paper discusses learning preferences from ordinal data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of low-rank matrices and convex relaxation techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses collaborative ranking, which is a common problem in recommender systems, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of optimization techniques and the focus on learning from data suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the focus on applications such as recommendation systems suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
